    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-04-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <head>No. 8.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DEC1" type="from">Clapp</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WH1" type="to">Hunter</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States
                                    Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                Ayres</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 15, 1873</date>. (Received May
                            21.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that General
                        Bartoloiné Mitre, having returned from his mission to Brazil, in which it
                        appears that he has been entirely successful in placing the delicate
                        questions between the two countries, arising out of the Paraguayan alliance,
                        on a satisfactory basis, has been dispatched to Paraguay, with full powers
                        to negotiate the treaty which the above-mentioned alliance contemplates.</p>
                <p>The Brazilian minister to this country, Baron <persName>de
                            Magallaens</persName>, has also gone to Paraguay to represent Brazilian
                        interests.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DEC1">DEXTER E. CLAPP</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
